All four fixes from the issue are implemented:

**A. Login page homepage link** (`frontend/login/index.html`) — Added "← Back to homepage" link to `/` so users have a UI path out after logout.

**B. Cache-Control headers** (`backend/main.py`) — Protected routes `/ops`, `/results`, `/my-jobs`, and `/worker-logs` now return `Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate` + `Pragma: no-cache`, preventing browsers from storing these pages in bfcache.

**C. bfcache pageshow handler** (`frontend/monitor/index.html`, `frontend/results/index.html`, `frontend/worker-logs/index.html`) — Each protected page now listens for `pageshow` with `event.persisted === true` and re-calls `/auth/me`, redirecting to `/login` if the session is gone.

**D. Cookie attribute matching** (`backend/main.py`) — `delete_cookie` now passes `path="/"` and `samesite="lax"` to match the original `set_cookie` call, ensuring the cookie is reliably cleared.
