**`frontend/public_page/index.html`**
- Added `if(!u){ window.location.href='/login'; return; }` in the existing `/auth/me` callback, so the page redirects client-side if somehow reached unauthenticated (defense-in-depth)

**`tests/smoke_test.py`**
- `/submit` unauthenticated → now expects `302` (was `200`)
- `POST /jobs` unauthenticated → now expects `401` (was `200`)
